  "root_text": {
    "iti29:0.1": "Itivuttaka 29 ",
    "iti29:0.2": "Dukanipāta ",
    "iti29:0.3": "Paṭhamavagga ",
    "iti29:0.4": "Sukhavihārasutta ",
    "iti29:1.1": "Vuttañhetaṁ bhagavatā vuttamarahatāti me sutaṁ: ",
    "iti29:2.1": "“Dvīhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu diṭṭheva dhamme sukhaṁ viharati avighātaṁ anupāyāsaṁ apariḷāhaṁ; ",
    "iti29:2.2": "kāyassa bhedā paraṁ maraṇā sugati pāṭikaṅkhā. ",
    "iti29:2.3": "Katamehi dvīhi? ",
    "iti29:2.4": "Indriyesu guttadvāratāya ca, bhojane mattaññutāya ca. ",
    "iti29:2.5": "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, dvīhi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu diṭṭheva dhamme sukhaṁ viharati avighātaṁ anupāyāsaṁ apariḷāhaṁ; ",
    "iti29:2.6": "kāyassa bhedā paraṁ maraṇā sugati pāṭikaṅkhā”ti. ",
    "iti29:2.7": "Etamatthaṁ bhagavā avoca. ",
    "iti29:2.8": "Tatthetaṁ iti vuccati: ",
    "iti29:3.1": "“Cakkhu sotañca ghānañca, ",
    "iti29:3.2": "jivhā kāyo tathā mano; ",
    "iti29:3.3": "Etāni yassa dvārāni, ",
    "iti29:3.4": "suguttāni ca bhikkhuno. ",
    "iti29:4.1": "Bhojanamhi ca mattaññū, ",
    "iti29:4.2": "indriyesu ca saṁvuto; ",
    "iti29:4.3": "Kāyasukhaṁ cetosukhaṁ, ",
    "iti29:4.4": "sukhaṁ so adhigacchati. ",
    "iti29:5.1": "Aḍayhamānena kāyena, ",
    "iti29:5.2": "Aḍayhamānena cetasā; ",
    "iti29:5.3": "Divā vā yadi vā rattiṁ, ",
    "iti29:5.4": "Sukhaṁ viharati tādiso”ti. ",
    "iti29:6.1": "Ayampi attho vutto bhagavatā, iti me sutanti. ",
    "iti29:6.2": "Dutiyaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "iti29:0.1": "So It Was Said 29 ",
    "iti29:0.2": "The Book of the Twos ",
    "iti29:0.3": "Chapter One ",
    "iti29:0.4": "Living in Happiness ",
    "iti29:1.1": "This was said by the Buddha, the Perfected One: that is what I heard. ",
    "iti29:2.1": "“Mendicants, when a mendicant has two qualities they live happily in this very life—without distress, anguish, and fever—",
    "iti29:2.2": "and when the body breaks up, after death, they can expect a good rebirth. ",
    "iti29:2.3": "What two? ",
    "iti29:2.4": "Guarding the sense doors and moderation in eating. ",
    "iti29:2.5": "When a mendicant possesses these two qualities they live happily in this very life—without distress, anguish, and fever—",
    "iti29:2.6": "and when the body breaks up, after death, they can expect a good rebirth.” ",
    "iti29:2.7": "The Buddha spoke this matter. ",
    "iti29:2.8": "On this it is said: ",
    "iti29:3.1": "“Eye, ear, nose, ",
    "iti29:3.2": "tongue, body, and likewise mind: ",
    "iti29:3.3": "a mendicant who makes these ",
    "iti29:3.4": "sense doors well guarded—",
    "iti29:4.1": "eating in moderation, ",
    "iti29:4.2": "restrained in the sense faculties—",
    "iti29:4.3": "reaps happiness ",
    "iti29:4.4": "both physical and mental. ",
    "iti29:5.1": "Not burning in body, ",
    "iti29:5.2": "not burning in mind, ",
    "iti29:5.3": "by day or by night ",
    "iti29:5.4": "such a person lives in happiness.” ",
    "iti29:6.1": "This too is a matter that was spoken by the Blessed One: that is what I heard. "
  },
